IE work for third party logins.

Discovered that IE will not access window.opener if site is
marked as 'trusted' in security settings or if the security
zone has changed for the window, and windowpostmessage can
fail unless a setTimout is used. Documented in comments.

Logout via viewer.

The RPC communication is simplified by replacing the setLoginSuccess
and setLoginFailure views/JS calls with setLoginStatus.  This single call will
relay whatever data the account has across the XDM RPC interface to
and the viewer will update accordingly.

Request additional information after a social login.

When the user login originates from omniauth using third party
authentication, show the user what their first and last name will be
displayed as and give them an option to update it.

Still needs additional checks on the account to determine whether or
not to run the account validations, and the input form needs
instructions.
